"THE VELVETEEN RABBIT," a musical of the children's classic by Margery Williams in which a young boy learns about closeness and friendship. Presented by Theaterworks/USA at the Promenade Theater, 2162 Broadway, at 76th Street, Manhattan, tomorrow and Sunday at 12:30 P.M. Tickets, $13 and $16. Information: (212) 677-5959.

"ALFRED THE DRAGON AND THE PHANTOM BALLOON STEALERS," the story of a shy dragon living in Central Park who becomes a detective. Performed by the Young People's Department of the New Media Repertory Company, 512 East 80th Street, Manhattan, tomorrow at 3 P.M. Admission is $6 for adults and $5 for children. Information: (212) 734-5195.